        The Config passed to this method should be the root Config as the builder requires access to the configuration keys grpc and coherence.

      • scope

        public String scope()
        Obtain the scope name of this session.

        The scope name is used to identify the ConfigurableCacheFactory on the server that owns the resources that this session connects to, for example maps, caches and topics.

        In most use cases the default scope name is used, but when the server has multiple scoped ConfigurableCacheFactory instances the scope name can be specified to link the session to a ConfigurableCacheFactory.

        Returns:
        the scope name of this session

      • addDeactivationListener

        public void addDeactivationListener​(com.oracle.coherence.grpc.client.DeactivationListener<GrpcRemoteSession> listener)
        Add a DeactivationListener that will be notified when this GrpcRemoteSession is closed.

        If this GrpcRemoteSession is already closed then the listener's DeactivationListener.destroyed(Object) method will be called immediately on the calling thread.

        Parameters:
        listener - the DeactivationListener to add
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the listener is null
